<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="583" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1749,2026]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Pale yellow. Ocelli and anterolateral margin of pronotum yellow, compound eyes yellow. Forewing white, costal margin with anterior, oblique and two posterior, transverse, black fasciae; second apical cell with black spot (Figs. 8, 23&amp; 38)</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1749,2026]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
Head angularly produced (
<figureCitation box="[495,579,1857,1882]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 30" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1872,1895]" captionTargetBox="[191,1328,199,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[179,1337,193,1828]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 30. Lateral habitus males of Sophonia species 16. S. bakeri Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 17. S. bifida Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 18. S. chandrai Meshram &amp; Ramamurthy; 19. S. complexa Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 20. S. complicata Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 21. S. illuminata (Distant); 22. S. insignis Distant 23. S. intricata sp. nov.; 24. S. keralica Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 25. S. linealis (Distant); 26. S. longicephala (Ahmed &amp; Mahmood); 27. S. longitudinalis (Distant); 28. S. modesta (Distant); 29. S. tridenta sp. nov; 30. S. vidarvya sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400214/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Ocelli near lateral margins of vertex, distance between eye and ocellus 3.4x diameter of ocellus. Vertex broadly concave and with irregular sculpturing anteriorly, posterior half glabrous (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 45" captionStartId="4.[157,270,1416,1439]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,212,1389]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1395]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 45. Head &amp; pronotum Sophonia species 31. S. bakeri Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 32. S. bifida Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 33. S. chandrai Meshram &amp; Ramamurthy; 34. S. complexa Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 35. S. complicata Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 36. S. illuminata (Distant); 37. S. insignis Distant 38. S. intricata sp. nov.; 39. S. keralica Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 40. S. linealis (Distant); 41. S. longicephala (Ahmed &amp; Mahmood); 42. S. longitudinalis (Distant); 43. S. modesta (Distant); 44. S. tridenta sp. nov.; 45. S. vidarvya sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400215/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
). Scutellum 0.7x as long as pronotum. Pronotum 0.8x longer than broad and as long as vertex (
<figureCitation box="[1247,1332,1929,1954]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 45" captionStartId="4.[157,270,1416,1439]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,212,1389]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1395]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 45. Head &amp; pronotum Sophonia species 31. S. bakeri Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 32. S. bifida Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 33. S. chandrai Meshram &amp; Ramamurthy; 34. S. complexa Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 35. S. complicata Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 36. S. illuminata (Distant); 37. S. insignis Distant 38. S. intricata sp. nov.; 39. S. keralica Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 40. S. linealis (Distant); 41. S. longicephala (Ahmed &amp; Mahmood); 42. S. longitudinalis (Distant); 43. S. modesta (Distant); 44. S. tridenta sp. nov.; 45. S. vidarvya sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400215/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1749,2026]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="583" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
Male genitalia. Pygofer triangular with few macrosetae in posterior half, caudodorsal angle roundly produced, below which small, slender, glabrous process arises, directed caudally, upcurved nearly at right angle at midlength (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 52" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1623,1646]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,417,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,409,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 52. Genitalia male Sophonia intricata sp. nov. 46. Male genitalia; 47. Style; 48. Connective; 49. Subgenital plate; 50 – 51. Aedeagus dorsdal view; 52. Aedeagus, lateral view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400216/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate wider medially than at apex and base, with median row of three stout macrosetae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 52" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1623,1646]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,417,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,409,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 52. Genitalia male Sophonia intricata sp. nov. 46. Male genitalia; 47. Style; 48. Connective; 49. Subgenital plate; 50 – 51. Aedeagus dorsdal view; 52. Aedeagus, lateral view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400216/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
). Style slender, preapical lobe robust, apophysis slender, apex with very long, beaklike extension (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1424,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 52" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1623,1646]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,417,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,409,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 52. Genitalia male Sophonia intricata sp. nov. 46. Male genitalia; 47. Style; 48. Connective; 49. Subgenital plate; 50 – 51. Aedeagus dorsdal view; 52. Aedeagus, lateral view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400216/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped with stem 
<date box="[527,561,224,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">3X</date>
as long as arms, apex expanded (
<figureCitation box="[961,1049,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 52" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1623,1646]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,417,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,409,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 52. Genitalia male Sophonia intricata sp. nov. 46. Male genitalia; 47. Style; 48. Connective; 49. Subgenital plate; 50 – 51. Aedeagus dorsdal view; 52. Aedeagus, lateral view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400216/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus complex, each dorsal apodome arm with winglike posteroventrally directed lobe in middle, long dorsomedian process extended mesa across midline, and slightly shorter caudal processcurved posteroventrad; aedeagal shaft strongly curved anteriorly, apex with pair of anteriorly directed processes (
<figureCitation box="[684,823,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 52" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1623,1646]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,417,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,409,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 52. Genitalia male Sophonia intricata sp. nov. 46. Male genitalia; 47. Style; 48. Connective; 49. Subgenital plate; 50 – 51. Aedeagus dorsdal view; 52. Aedeagus, lateral view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400216/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Figs. 50–52</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
