<subSubSection box="[199,1149,1824,1849]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1716,2029]" box="[199,1149,1824,1849]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1824,1849]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name alludes to very complicated structure of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="583" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1716,2029]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1860,1885]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[330,548,1860,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intricata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[330,548,1860,1884]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Sophonia intricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[564,662,1860,1885]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[564,662,1860,1885]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath &amp; Wesley" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Wesley" box="[843,1293,1860,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis box="[843,1004,1860,1884]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">S. complicata</emphasis>
Viraktamath &amp; Wesley
</taxonomicName>
in external appearance (Fig. 5), but differs in the structure of the male genitalia (features of 
<taxonomicName box="[1048,1201,1896,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis box="[1048,1201,1896,1920]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">S. complicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parentheses):style slender, preapical lobe robust, apophysis slender, apex with very long beaklike extension (style with elongate, slender, praeapicallobe, apophysis slender avicephaliform); aedeagus with shaft relatively slender, tubular (broadly expanded distally in both lateral and posteroventral views; 
<figureCitation box="[812,949,2004,2029]" captionStart="FIGURES 67 – 79" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1906,1929]" captionTargetBox="[231,1364,216,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[204,1372,207,1857]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 67 – 79. Species of Sophonia, 67 – 73. Sophonia complicata Viraktamath &amp; Wesley 67. Male genitalia; 68, 69. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 70. Aedeagus anterior view; 71. Connective; 72. Style; 73. Subgenital plate. 74 – 79. S. longicephala (Ahmed &amp; Mahmood) 74. Pygofer; 75, 76. Aedeagus lateral &amp; anterior view; 77. Connective; 78. Style; 79. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400219/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">Figs. 67–69</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
